cess()" function (and clean up late,<br />obviously).<br /><br />Then, instead of that "struct multiprocess_signals" thing, just add a<br />"struct hlist_node node" to "struct signal" itself, and add it to the<br />multiprocess hlist there.<br /><br />And then you can just remove it in bad_fork_cleanup_signal.<br /><br />Does this make "struct signal" a bit larger? Yes, but it's not a huge<br />deal. We *could* make is some union with existing fields if we cared.<br /><br />But I think it would make the code *much* more understandable, and it<br />would allow us to not have that "sigpending" copy, because you can<br />just populate the final "signal-&gt;shared_pending" directly.<br /><br />Hmm?<br /><br />             Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
